The paper deals with the problem of secure estimation in the presence of nonstochastic disturbances and uncertain channels, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY). The security aspect of the problem suggests that it may also belong to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. The use of block-encoding and numerical examples suggests that it may also be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG).
